Exception_LEVEL_CD

SQL Script
Parameter
Value
SQL Script
update Outbound_Src_synygy_geo_master_outbound
set Level_cd=case

when Level_cd='Sub-Terr'
then Level_cd
when Level_cd like 'terr%'
then 'Territory'
when Level_cd like 'div%'
then 'Division'
else Level_cd
end

update Outbound_Src_synygy_geo_master_outbound set Level_cd=case when Level_cd='Sub-Terr' then Level_cd when Level_cd like 'terr%' then 'Territory' when Level_cd like 'div%' then 'Division' else Level_cd end

Geo: Create Exception Rule

Calculator
Parameter
Value
Include Input Columns
Yes
Calculations
CASE WHEN "geo_id" = '504' AND ("lower_algn_struc_cd" ='' OR "lower_algn_struc_cd" is null) THEN
'LSLM'
ELSE
"lower_algn_struc_cd"
END, ALGN_STRUC_CD_EXCEPTION_RULE, CASE WHEN "level_cd" IN ('TLP2 Terr', 'TLP4 Terr', 'TALP1 Terr','TLP1 Terr','TLP3 Terr','TALP4 Terr','TALP2 Terr','TALP3 Terr') THEN
'Territory'
WHEN "level_cd" ilike 'Sub-Div' THEN
'Division'
ELSE
"level_cd"
END, LEVEL_CD_EXCEPTION_RULE, CASE WHEN "level_cd" iLIKE 'Nation' THEN
"lower_algn_struc_cd"
ELSE
"geo_id"
END, GEO_ID_EXCEPTION_RULE

Job: Archive Outbound Global Function

Add TimeStamp & Get File,Table Information from context of the job run

Python Script
Parameter
Value
Script
import datetime

x = datetime.datetime.now()
x=str(x).split('.')

x=x[0]
print('time_stamp :'+str(x))
print('Archive_temp_current_table :'+str(Archive_temp_current_table))
print('Archive_temp_current_file :'+str(Archive_temp_current_file))

Archive_temp_current_file=Archive_temp_current_file+'_'+x+'__'
print('Archive_temp_current_file upt :'+str(Archive_temp_current_file))
context.updateVariable('Archive_temp_current_file', str(Archive_temp_current_file))
print('Archive_type :'+Archive_type)


#dynamically change path for Archive
if Archive_type=='ONEMD':
S3_temp_Archive_Location=S3_ONEMD_Archive_Location
print('Archive Locations :'+str(S3_temp_Archive_Location))
elif Archive_type=='MDM21':
S3_temp_Archive_Location=S3_MDM21_Archive_Location
print('Archive Locations :'+str(S3_temp_Archive_Location))
else:
S3_temp_Archive_Location=S3_EUSS_Archive_Location
print('Archive Locations :'+str(S3_temp_Archive_Location))
